{"TopicId":177980,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"How to set the initial state of the vessel","CreatedByName":"GYskyfall","CreatedById":191508,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-01T07:37:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"GYskyfall","CreatedById":191508,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-01T07:37:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat should I do if I want to\u00A0\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eput a spaceship in the designated position and give it the designated initial state such as,speed(including direction and magnitude), or that is just impossible\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-01T07:44:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe HyperEdit mod will allow you to instantly reposition a spaceship anywhere in the Kerbol system, adjust its resources etc.:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5763372147\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/34785-144-hyperedit-v158-july-10-2018-cheat-teleporter-orbitplanet-editor-more/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GYskyfall","CreatedById":191508,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-01T07:46:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223443276\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177980\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221535787854\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sumghai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, sumghai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe HyperEdit mod will allow you to instantly reposition a spaceship anywhere in the Kerbol system, adjust its resources etc.:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed143002346\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/34785-144-hyperedit-v158-july-10-2018-cheat-teleporter-orbitplanet-editor-more/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:226px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut it can\u0027t set the speed at diferent direction at the same time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-09-01T07:47:55Z\u0022 title=\u002209/01/2018 07:47  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 1, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by sumghai\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ESeparated reply from actual quote\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-01T07:49:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223443277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177980\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221535788002\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022191508\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GYskyfall\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, GYskyfall said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut it can\u0027t set the speed at diferent direction at the same time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s definitely a menu option to adjust the \u003Cem\u003Evelocity\u003C/em\u003E (speed \u003Cem\u003Eand\u003C/em\u003E direction) of spacecraft at any location.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-09-01T07:49:51Z\u0022 title=\u002209/01/2018 07:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 1, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by sumghai\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EFix minor spelling mistake\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GYskyfall","CreatedById":191508,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-01T07:51:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223443279\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177980\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221535788168\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sumghai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, sumghai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s definitely a menu option to adjust the \u003Cem\u003Evelocity\u003C/em\u003E (speed \u003Cem\u003Eand\u003C/em\u003E direction) of spacecraft at any location.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut not at the same time, you only can set one by one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-01T07:58:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223443281\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177980\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221535788302\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022191508\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GYskyfall\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, GYskyfall said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut not at the same time, you only can set one by one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nOpen HyperEdit (Alt-H)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSelect Orbit Editor \u0026gt; Velocity\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSet the Speed value\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nChoose the Direction (Prograde, Normal, Radial, North, East, Up - use negative Speed values if you want Retrograde, Antinormal, Antiradial, South, West, Down)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nClick Apply\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat exactly are you trying to do with your spacecraft? Setting it on a specific orbit?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GYskyfall","CreatedById":191508,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-01T08:30:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223443284\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177980\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221535788731\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sumghai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, sumghai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nOpen HyperEdit (Alt-H)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSelect Orbit Editor \u0026gt; Velocity\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSet the Speed value\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nChoose the Direction (Prograde, Normal, Radial, North, East, Up - use negative Speed values if you want Retrograde, Antinormal, Antiradial, South, West, Down)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nClick Apply\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat exactly are you trying to do with your spacecraft? Setting it on a specific orbit?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfor example ,in a coordinate \u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ECoordinate System\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E ,vector speed V is composed of Vx,Vy,Vz. If you want set a vector V, you should set Vx,Vy,Vz at the sme time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHyperedit just set one direction during an \u0022apply\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-01T09:10:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223443290\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177980\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221535790617\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022191508\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GYskyfall\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n38 minutes ago, GYskyfall said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfor example ,in a coordinate \u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ECoordinate System\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E ,vector speed V is composed of Vx,Vy,Vz. If you want set a vector V, you should set Vx,Vy,Vz at the sme time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHyperedit just set one direction during an \u0022apply\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s because the stock game itself doesn\u0027t support arbitrary velocity vectors. Even if you could specify them, orbital mechanics immediately override them anyway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-05T10:59:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can do this indirectly, through the orbit editor. Your Cartesian state vector corresponds to a certain set of Keplerian elements. Setting these elements all at once is possible through Hyperedit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tyko","CreatedById":164179,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-05T21:55:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCouldn\u0027t you even do it in the F12 menu? Define the orbit and parameters like velocity \u0026amp; direction of travel will be determined by your orbit and the body you\u0027re orbiting...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(actually this might be what \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/145504-sharpy/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022145504\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/145504-sharpy/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sharpy\u003C/a\u003E said above, more precisely, when he mentioned Keplerian elements)\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-09-05T21:56:00Z\u0022 title=\u002209/05/2018 09:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 5, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Tyko\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-05T22:40:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this for the Making History expansion or something you\u0027re trying to do in the base game?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}